<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA BIAS ON ABORTION ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for the series. Since pro-life sentiment is as intense and widespread 
in this country as pro-choice sentiment is, how does it happen that journalists 
in big-city news organizations "don't seem to have many friends or colleagues 
who oppose abortion," so that they aren't even aware of the magnitude of 
pro-life rallies like the one in April? 
</P>
<P>
What kind of hiring and promotion practices are producing whole staffs with the 
same blind spot? What other issues are being screened out in the same way, 
while the media spotlights converge momentarily on broccoli? 
</P>
<P>
FAYE JEANIS 
</P>
<P>
San Jose 
</P>
</TEXT>
