<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA BIAS ON ABORTION ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The articles were outstanding. I can only hope that this is a new beginning for 
The Times and other media. I can only hope that this isn't just a bone thrown 
to the dog so that he will stop barking and go away. 
</P>
<P>
All any "pro-life advocate" has ever asked is that there is fair reporting. 
That's all that is asked now. 
</P>
<P>
The "liberal media" and the "conservative anti-abortion activists" need to 
consider two things when they are speaking out. Women who find themselves in a 
crisis pregnancy situation need compassion, understanding and very practical 
help. And unborn babies who are in danger of being aborted also need advocates 
to speak out in their defense. Unborn children are valuable and they have the 
right to our compassion and protection. 
</P>
<P>
GAIL M. HAMILTON 
</P>
<P>
Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
