<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEDIA BIAS ON ABORTION ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Can I believe my eyes? Just yesterday you finished an excellent, in-depth 
series by Shaw on the extent of blatant pro-abortion bias in the media. Today, 
as I open my paper (July 5, Page B2), I see that the listing of Los Angeles 
area hot lines includes (of course) an abortion referral service but does not 
include any of the pro-life agencies which exist to render medical, financial 
and emotional support to those courageous young women who refuse to abort their 
developing children. It kind of makes you wonder, doesn't it? 
</P>
<P>
ANN K. GRIVICH 
</P>
<P>
West Covina 
</P>
