<P>
Good Grief, Not a Grown-Up, Charlie Brown!: Forty years after starting his 
"Peanuts" comic strip, Charles Schulz plans to introduce an adult for the first 
time into the fantasy world populated by Snoopy and several children -- but 
only on a television special to be aired next year. The adult will have only a 
small part and be a character that works at a puppy farm where Snoopy and his 
brothers, Spike and Olaf, meet for a reunion. GREG BRAXTON 
