<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Promoters Pose Labeling Threat: The North American Concert Promoters Assn. 
(NACP) has announced that it will cancel its New Orleans convention this fall 
if the governor signs into law a bill requiring labels on explicit records. 
</P>
<P>
The threat was the latest complaint about the bill, which would be the first 
state law of its kind if passed. "If this bill becomes law, concert promoters, 
recording artists and community retailers will be driven out of business," NACP 
Director Carl Freed said in a statement. "They are being made scapegoats by 
soap box politicians." GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
