<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: FILLMORE; 
</P>
<P>
CONTRACT RENEWED FOR BUS SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fillmore City Council has renewed its agreement with the Fillmore Area 
Transit Company to provide bus service within Fillmore and around the county 
for fiscal 1990-1991. 
</P>
<P>
The transit company offers bus service five days a week to Piru, Santa Paula 
and Ventura, including a direct commuter service to the County Government 
Center. The company also offers service around the city of Fillmore. 
</P>
<P>
Except for the route within city limits, the county subsidizes between 60% and 
80% of the cost of the bus service. The city will pay $101,600 for service in 
1990-91, nearly half its allotment of state Transportation Development funds. 
JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</TEXT>
