<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW IMMIGRANT KILLED BY TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Guatemalan woman was killed in Van Nuys when she was struck by a pickup truck 
at Van Nuys Boulevard and Valerio Street, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
A suspect, Oscar Valdez, 31, of Burbank, fled the Saturday night accident but 
later turned himself in, said Officer Bill Mulvihill of the Los Angeles Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
The pedestrian, also 31, arrived in Los Angeles three days ago from Guatemala, 
Mulvihill said. Her identity was withheld until relatives could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
Valdez was charged with vehicular manslaughter. He told police he did not see 
the woman, or the traffic signal changing, and fled because he panicked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
