<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARSHALL PLACED ON DISABLED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Marshall of the New York Mets spent Saturday night at a Cincinnati 
hospital and underwent tests for a condition diagnosed as inflammation of the 
gastrointestinal tract. 
</P>
<P>
Marshall, 30, who has played in 53 games for the Mets this season, is being 
placed on the disabled list for 15 days, Met Manager Bud Harrelson said. 
</P>
<P>
He was released Sunday from the hospital, Harrelson said. Marshall was 
hospitalized Saturday, one day after he and Harrelson had a loud clubhouse 
argument. 
</P>
<P>
Marshall has been unhappy in a part-time role since being acquired from the 
Dodgers in the off-season and said he wants to be traded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
