<HEADLINE>
<P>
HERRMANN STILL UNSIGNED BY RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Mark Herrmann, whose Ram future has been in doubt since the 
acquisition of Chuck Long from the Detroit Lions, remains unsigned as 
quarterback Jim Everett and selected running backs report to camp today. 
</P>
<P>
Herrmann, 31, was supposed to report, too, but no deal had been completed as of 
Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
Ram sources said that in Herrmann's case, a contract could be worked out before 
today's practice. 
</P>
<P>
Herrmann's chances of making this year's team appear to depend on whether the 
Rams keep three quarterbacks on their roster. 
</P>
<P>
In other news, Mike McDonald, the team's snapper on punts and field goals, has 
been signed to a one-year contract, leaving the Rams with seven unsigned 
veterans, including Pro Bowl linebacker Kevin Greene. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
