<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NBC HIRES FRATELLO AS NBA ANALYST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Fratello, who quit as the Atlanta Hawks' coach last April 23, will take 
the NBA analyst's job with NBC Sports that Detroit Piston Coach Chuck Daly 
turned down in favor of trying to win a third straight NBA title. 
</P>
<P>
NBC said Fratello had signed a multiyear contract at an undisclosed sum to join 
Marv Albert and Bob Costas on the NBA broadcast team. Former Laker coach Pat 
Riley is NBC's studio host. 
</P>
<P>
Fratello spent seven seasons as Hawk coach but quit after a 41-41 season in 
which Atlanta failed to make the playoffs for the first time in five years. He 
had a 323-251 record as Atlanta's head coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
