<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's Kubota Sued for $25 Million: The suit claims that Kubota Ltd. of Japan 
forced Ardent Computer of Sunnyvale into a merger with Stellar Computer of 
Massachusetts to weaken Ardent and gain its technology. 
</P>
<P>
The suit was filed by company founders Allen Michels and Matthew Sanders. 
However, the chief executive of Stardent disassociated the supercomputer 
company from the lawsuit, saying it was an individual action by Michels and 
Sanders. Kubota, Ardent's largest shareholder and creditor, said it would 
defend itself vigorously against the charges. 
</P>
