BATTLING THE MEDFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Department of Food and Agriculture will conduct aerial spraying 
of malathion tonight beginning at 9, weather permitting. 
</P>
<P>
Area: 15 square miles encompassing parts of Arcadia, El Monte, Rosemead, San 
Gabriel, South El Monte and Temple City; 16 square miles in the Los Angeles 
area encompassing Atwater, Glassell Park, Mt. Washington and parts of Eagle 
Rock, Glendale and Highland Park. 
</P>
<P>
Precautions: Stay indoors, keep animals indoors, wash animal dishes and toys 
left outside, cover cars, keep doors and windows closed. 
</P>
<P>
