P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIET GAS PIPELINE RUPTURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pipeline has ruptured in the Ural mountains, spewing 735 million cubic feet 
of natural gas into the air, the official Tass press agency reported today. 
</P>
<P>
In a separate incident this weekend, a corroded oil pipeline sprang a leak, the 
oil caught fire, and 27 wells had to be shut down, Tass said. 
</P>
<P>
An official blamed poor construction and maintenance for the accidents. 
</P>
<P>
In the first incident, the pipeline rupture halted supplies of more than 3,500 
million cubic feet of natural gas coming from the Tyumen region, 900 miles east 
of Moscow. 
</P>
