<P>
PAULEY LEARNS TO BANISH HIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jane Pauley has had it all -- even hives. 
</P>
<P>
The former "Today" co-host, now a fill-in anchor on the "NBC Nightly News," 
told New York magazine that at age 7, she broke into hives after being punished 
for another child's prank. 
</P>
<P>
"My eyes swelled up or something glamorous like that and my mother had to take 
me home from school," she said. "Later she took me to a specialist who said 
that I was a nervous child who would have to be careful my whole life." 
</P>
<P>
Pauley added: 'This is good information for a kid who is anxious about life. 
Instead I grew up to do live television. I think it's kind of funny." 
</P>
<P>
Pauley got over her problems with hives and headaches years ago, the magazine 
reported in its July 23 issue. 
