<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
BABY ENTERS GOVERNOR'S MANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JACKSON, Miss. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wife of Gov. Ray Mabus has given birth to a girl, the first child born to 
an incumbent Mississippi governor since the turn of the century. 
</P>
<P>
The girl, who was named Elisabeth Hamilton, was delivered by Cesarean section 
Sunday at Baptist Medical Center, and weighed 9 pounds, 8 1/2 ounces. 
</P>
<P>
The mother, Julie, and the child were doing well, the governor said. 
</P>
<P>
"Daddy almost didn't make it through, but Mom did fine," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Asked how the birth compared with being elected governor, Mabus said, "This is 
so much better than anything I've ever done in my life . . . no comparison." 
</P>
<P>
The last baby born to a Mississippi governor in office was a daughter of Gov. 
A. H. Longino, who served from 1900 to 1904. 
</P>
</TEXT>
